Congress never authorized the US military to support the brutal Saudi Arabian assault on Yemen, where Human Rights Watch warns that “the world’s largest humanitarian crisis” is now unfolding.
It is about Yemen, of course, but it is also about the role of Congress.
The president’s veto forces an existential choice on members of Congress, no matter how they voted on the initial resolution.